BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 662.00 Tm (?# Methods And System Description) Tj ET
BT /F2 15.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 626.00 Tm (Abstract) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 596.00 Tm (CytoCV is a web-based analysis system for DeltaVision microscopy of mitotic yeast cells. The) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 582.00 Tm (platform integrates authenticated web workflows, DeltaVision-specific metadata parsing, Mask) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 568.00 Tm (R-CNN-based segmentation, plugin-scoped per-cell quantification, and retention-aware result) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 554.00 Tm (management in a single Django application. The current codebase supports four logical) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 540.00 Tm (channel roles \(DIC, Blue, Red, and Green\), but only DIC is universally required. Additional) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 526.00 Tm (fluorescence requirements are derived from the selected analysis plugins and optional) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 512.00 Tm (upload-time validation policy.) Tj ET
BT /F2 15.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 476.00 Tm (System Objective) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 446.00 Tm (The system is designed to reduce manual analysis effort while preserving the relationship) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 432.00 Tm (between source microscopy stacks, derived segmentation artifacts, and exported measurements.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 418.00 Tm (CytoCV therefore treats run configuration, channel mapping, scale context, and plugin) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 404.00 Tm (selection as first-class workflow state rather than transient UI detail.) Tj ET
BT /F2 15.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 368.00 Tm (Input Model) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 338.00 Tm (CytoCV ingests DeltaVision \(.dv\) files that can be interpreted as channel stacks. The) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 324.00 Tm (implementation recognizes four logical channel roles:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 302.00 Tm (- ) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 70.00 302.00 Tm (DIC, used for structural segmentation and CNN preprocessing) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 284.00 Tm (- ) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 70.00 284.00 Tm (Blue, used for legacy nucleus-related measurements) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 266.00 Tm (- ) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 70.00 266.00 Tm (Red, used for red-signal contour and intensity measurements) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 248.00 Tm (- ) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 70.00 248.00 Tm (Green, used for green-signal contour, intensity, and dot-classification measurements) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 228.00 Tm (The software does not require all four roles in every run. The minimum baseline requirement) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 214.00 Tm (is DIC. The default modern configuration requires DIC, Red, and Green. Blue becomes required) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 200.00 Tm (only when a legacy Blue-channel legacy plugin is selected or when full-wavelength validation) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 186.00 Tm (is enabled.) Tj ET
BT /F2 15.00 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 150.00 Tm (Validation Logic) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 120.00 Tm (Upload-time validation is controlled by the effective requirement set assembled in) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 106.00 Tm (core.views.experiment and core.metadata_processing.error_handling.dv_validation.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10.50 Tf 1 0 0 1 54.00 82.00 Tm (The effective required channels are formed as:) Tj ET
endstream
